Dear friends and colleagues,=0A=
=0A=
We're delighted to announce the Applied Category Theory 2018 Adjoint School=
, an initiative to bring early career researchers into the applied category=
  theory community.=0A=
=0A=
The Adjoint School comprises two phases: (1) an online reading seminar base=
d on the recent Kan Extension Seminars, and (2) a four day research week at=
  the Lorentz Center, Leiden, The Netherlands. Participants will also be inv=
ited to attend Applied Category Theory 2018, which will be held immediately=
  following the research week, also at the Lorentz Center.=0A=
=0A=
During the school, participants will work under the mentorship of four ment=
ors, on one of the following research projects:=0A=
=0A=
- John Baez: Semantics for open Petri nets and reaction networks=0A=
- Aleks Kissinger: Unification of the logic of causality=0A=
- Martha Lewis: Compositional approaches to linguistics and cognition=0A=
- Pawel Sobocinski: Modelling of open and interconnected systems=0A=
=0A=
The online seminar begins in early January 2018, and will run until the res=
earch week begins on April 23rd, 2018. Applied Category Theory 2018 will be=
  held April 30th to May 4th.=0A=
=0A=
Applications to participate in the school are now open. For more details, i=
ncluding how to apply, please see here:=0A=
=0A=
http://www.appliedcategorytheory.org/school=0A=
=0A=
or contact the organisers below. Applications close November 1st.=0A=
=0A=
Kind regards,=0A=
=0A=
Brendan Fong (bfo@mit.edu)=0A=
Nina Otter (otter@maths.ox.ac.uk)=


